4  \n  \n### pont.yaml\n\n|\n\n### pont.yaml\n\n| Update pont.yaml| Apr 25, 2024  \n  \n## Repository files navigation\n\n# Pont\n\nPont is a simple project template generator and loader. You can generate\ntemplates and load them from Git repositories or local directories.\n\n## Installation\n\nCurrently, pont can only be installed using cargo.\n\n    \n    \n    cargo install pont\n\n## Usage\n\n### Generate a template\n\n    \n    \n    pont new <template-name> # to create a new directory\n\nor\n\n    \n    \n    pont init # to use the current directory\n\n### Build a project from a template\n\n    \n    \n    pont build --name <template-name> --from <source>\n\n## Example\n\n    \n    \n    pont new rust_server_template cd ./rust_server_template cargo init cargo add axum tokio serde serde_json git remote add origin <your-remote-repo> git add . git commit -m \"Base project\" git push cd ../ pont build --name cool_rust_app --from <your-remote-repo>\n\n## About\n\nCreate and load project templates.\n\nwww.soup.dev/pont\n\n### Topics\n\ntemplate project-template project\n\n### Resources\n\nReadme\n\n### License\n\nMIT license\n\nActivity\n\nCustom properties\n\n### Stars\n\n1 star\n\n### Watchers\n\n1 watching\n\n### Forks\n\n0 forks\n\nReport repository\n\n## Releases\n\nNo releases published\n\n## Languages\n\n  * Rust 100.0%\n\n## Footer\n\n\u00a9 2024 GitHub, Inc.\n\nYou can\u2019t perform that action at this time.\n\n", "frontpage": false}
